name: Blackened Chicken Strips
author: Yoly
summary: Ready in under 20 minutes, this is the perfect dinner to make when in a hurry. Spiced up by the addition of cayenne pepper but cooled down thanks to the dry ranch dressing.
ingredients: 2 tablespoons dry ranch dressing mix (such as Hidden Valley Ranch®)
½ tablespoon chili powder, or to taste
directions: Mix dry ranch dressing, chili powder, cayenne, and black pepper in a small bowl
Coat chicken tenders with dry rub mix
Heat oil in a cast iron skillet over medium heat
Place chicken tenders into the hot oil
Cook over medium heat without moving to blacken skin, about 4 minutes
Turn chicken and cook until chicken is no longer pink in the center and the juices run clear, about 2 more minutes
